Paper: hep-th/0012120

Date: 2000-12-14

Title: High-precision estimates of critical quantities by means of improved

HamiltoniansAuthors: M. Campostrini, M. Hasenbusch, A. Pelissetto, P. Rossi and E. Vicari

Comments: 7 pages, contribution to the 2nd Conference on the Exact

Renormalization Group, Roma, September 2000Journal-ref: Int.J.Mod.Phys. A16 (2001) 2009-2014

Three-dimensional spin models of the Ising and XY universality classes arestudied by a combination of high-temperature expansions and Monte Carlosimulations applied to improved Hamiltonians. The critical exponents and thecritical equation of state are determined to very high precision.